By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has confirmed 152 new cases of  COVID-19 in Nigeria. According to the report released via it’s twitter handle late Tuesday, this brings total confirmed cases 64,336 out ot which 60,333 have been treated and discharged from various isolation centres across the country. The health agency also reported that 1,160 lives have been lost to COVID-19 related complications since the index case was recorded in Nigeria on 27th February, 2020. The NCDC further stated that the 152 new cases were recorded from 9 states including the FCT as follows: Lagos-93FCT-21Oyo-15Rivers-11Bauchi-7Kwara-2Bayelsa-1Edo-1Plateau-1 It gave the state by state breakdown of total confirmed cases thus: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Sunday confirmed 111 new cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria. The health agency which disclosed this via it's twitter handle account said that the fresh infections were recorded from eight states including the FCT as follows: Lagos-49… November 2, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The total confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria hit 59,001 as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) reported 153 new fresh infections on Thursday. Similarly, the NCDC report released via it's twitter handle account further said that the total of 50, 452… October 2, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Lagos State, the epicentre of COVID-19 in Nigeria recorded 106 infections on Friday as the Centre for Disease Control confirmed 170 new cases of the novel virus. This renewed upsurge in number of infections in Lagos may not be unconnected with the large… October 31, 2020 In "Top Stories"